post_text: What an amazing achievement by one of our Barton Creek Elementary students! Advika's artwork was one of 34 out of 42k submissions to be included in all U.S. editions of J.K. Rowling's #Ickabog when it comes out in Nov. She will receive a signed copy and BCE will receive $650 worth of books from Scholastic! #EISDShines
shared_text:
THEICKABOG.COM
Competition - The Ickabog

Barton Creek Elementary Library
August 25 at 3:40 PM ·

In June and July, J.K. Rowling released a serialized version of a new book called The Ickabog. Rowling simultaneously hosted an illustration competition for children to create art inspired by each chapter of the book. There were 42,000 art submissions in the U.S. and only 34 illustrations were chosen.

We learned today that one of our very own own fourth graders, Advika, was chosen as a winner! She will receive a copy The Ickabog signed by J.K. Rowling and her art will be included in all U.S. editions of the book when it is published on November 10th! The contest winners also get to choose a school or public library to receive $650 worth of books from Scholastic. Advika has generously chosen the BCE Library to be the beneficiary of this awesome gift!

Congratulations, Advika! We are so amazingly proud of you!

post_text: The #EanesBoard voted to hire Dr. Mark Gooden as a Diversity, Equity and Inclusion (DEI) consultant for the 2020-21 school year. Dr. Gooden will lead the process to enhance community, staff and student racial awareness and to cultivate an environment of understanding unique similarities and differences. Under Dr. Gooden’s guidance, the district will address social justice and racism in Eanes ISD as well as shape staff professional development plans throughout the school year. The district will also explore ideas around the selection of a community advisory group to help guide the district’s efforts. Read more: https://is.gd/PPzHXF

Eanes ISD will follow the Austin-Travis County order banning in-person instruction and will offer 100-percent remote learning through at least Sept. 7. We are ready to implement plans made over the summer to ensure a more robust, sustainable and developmentally appropriate online instructional experience for students in all grades.

Read more: https://is.gd/yEqxwg

Note: the Eanes ISD Board will see a report on evolving plans, enrollment updates and preliminary data from the Fall Options application at the July 21 meeting.

The Options Application window opens Monday at 8am and closes July 8th at 5pm. Information on the R2R options and plan is online: www.eanesisd.net/R2R.

post_text: Here's a smile for a Thursday...these talented Forest Trail Elementary 5th graders created this video to share with area assisted living facilities. Tip: watch the very end for a special treat! #EISDShines
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Forest Trail 5th Grade - What a Wonderful World

Forest Trail Elementary
April 22 at 2:35 PM ·

When Forest Trail students see an opportunity to make a someone have a better day, they do it!

For the safety of their residents, nursing homes aren’t allowing visitors, and many residents are especially lonely, missing their loved ones during this isolation period. Sing-alongs to the "Golden Oldies" are weekly activities at most retirement communities. It's heartwarming to see the joy of all of the residents singing, many knowing all of the words to the songs - even the patients with dementia and Alzheimers. Songs spark memories and lift spirits.

We hoped "What a Wonderful World," by Louis Armstrong would also be an important, positive message for our students during this difficult time - helping them appreciate the beauty that surrounds all of us.

Thank you to all of our students who participated, Mrs. Hitt for her leadership, and Danni Hitt for the video production.

If you have loved ones that might find joy in our video, please share with their facility's administration.

#FalconFinest #BeKind

https://youtu.be/7yRiiQuTwrk

post_text: Dr. Leonard's message to students before their "first" day of (remote) school.
text: Dr. Leonard's message to students before their "first" day of (remote) school.

post_text:
Megan Grant, a freshman at Westlake High School, wrote this song when she was a 7th grader at Hill Country Middle School for a GT passion project to show how music could be used to empathize with children in difficult situations. In January 2020, Megan’s mother offered this song to a friend who is an educator in China as a way to comfort his students when they were first quarantined during the COVID-19 outbreak. Little did they know these very children featured in the video would soon be affected by the pandemic and urged to stay at home themselves.

All the children featured in the video are Eanes ISD students and the choir singing the last chorus is none other than the HCMS choir. #EISDShines
text:
Megan Grant, a freshman at Westlake High School, wrote this song when she was a 7th grader at Hill Country Middle School for a GT passion project to show how music could be used to empathize with children in difficult situations. In January 2020, Megan’s mother offered this song to a friend who is an educator in China as a way to comfort his students when they were first quarantined during the COVID-19 outbreak. Little did they know these very children featured in the video would soon be affected by the pandemic and urged to stay at home themselves.

All the children featured in the video are Eanes ISD students and the choir singing the last chorus is none other than the HCMS choir. #EISDShines

post_text:
To slow the spread of the virus and safeguard the well-being of students and staff, Eanes ISD will suspend normal operations Monday, March 23 through Sunday, April 5. Students and staff should not return to campuses until they are notified.

During this two-week period, all Eanes ISD facilities will be closed for instruction and all other functions until further notice, including UIL events, athletics, rentals, field trips, after-school programs, childcare and other campus activities. All facility rentals during spring break until April 5 are canceled.

Read Dr. Leonard’s letter here: https://is.gd/5sKZXg

Due to the possibility of inclement weather, Eanes ISD is canceling all after-school activities, including all athletic competitions. Groups that have already left for overnight trips out of the area will continue as planned and district and campus personnel will monitor those activities.

Easy Care will still operate, but we ask parents to be mindful of the potential inclement weather and arrive to pick up children at the earliest opportunity.

We acknowledge the inconvenience this may cause and we appreciate your understanding of our need to prioritize the safety of our students and staff.

All staff members should work with their supervisors, but try to leave as soon as all students are gone.

All Eanes ISD schools will start late today due to inclement weather and potentially icy roads. Bus pick-up and school start times will be exactly two hours later than the normal start time. Child Development Centers at Barton Creek, Forest Trail and Valley View will start at 9am. For further information and updates throughout the day, please check our website, eanesisd.net.

Staff should report two hours later than their normal start time. Custodial and maintenance staff will receive additional information from supervisors.

We acknowledge the inconvenience a late start may cause and we appreciate your understanding of our need to prioritize the safety of our students and staff.

Westlake High School celebrates its 50th anniversary and Homecoming with several events beginning Friday. The weekend of events includes tours of the school, a former WHS staff lunch. an alumni association tailgate and culminates with the Homecoming volleyball game against Del Valle at 6:30pm and the football game at 7:30pm (SOLD OUT).

Saturday, the Eanes Education Foundation will host the Inaugural Distinguished Alumni Brunch, which will recognize:

Rich Riley '92
Former CEO of Shazam & Co-Founder of HomePoint

Drew Brees '97
Super Bowl MVP-Winning Quarterback & Philanthropist

Alexis Jones '01
Author, Activist & Founder of I Am That Girl & ProtectHer

Outstanding Young Alumni
Matt Nader '07
Advocate of Sudden Cardiac Arrest Awareness

Honorary Alumni
Toody Byrd
Longtime & Beloved WHS Guidance Counselor

KXAN News meteorologist and WHS alum, David Yeomans hosts the event with guest speaker WHS alum Alexis Jones.

Westlake junior Ryan Mulcahy created the 50th-anniversary logo after a school-wide logo contest.

Spreading the theme of kindness, empathy and resiliency... the entire Hill Country Middle School community (students, staff, parents, bus drivers, custodians, cafeteria staff, etc.) is reading the book House Arrest by KA Holt.

This initiative is part of #OneBookOneCommunity, where every Tuesday and Thursday in October, HCMS students will read the book together and participate in activities surrounding the themes of the book. After finishing the book, students will plan their own service project to provide kindness bags for family members of children in the hospital. The school will also get a visit from the author on December 2. #EISDShines #EISDSEL #EISDKindness

There has been an increase of vaping stories in the news recently. See info below so you may talk to your student on the dangers of vaping.

• As of September 12, 2019, 33 state health department have reported more than 450 cases of severe lung disease associated with the use of e-cigarettes.
• Six deaths have been confirmed in California, Illinois, Indiana, Minnesota, Oregon and Kansas.
• The median age of those affected is 19, making this a teen and adult problem.
• More cases are expected as CDC and FDA advisories are encouraging the medical community to report suspected cases.

More info and resources:
https://is.gd/UYrhdX

post_text: Congratulations to all of our WHS Business Incubator students on their phenomenal business concepts! #EISDShines
shared_text:
Westlake High School
May 29, 2019 at 9:52 AM ·

Westlake High School juniors who formed SipSafe as part of the WHS Business Incubator course won $15,000 at the 3rd Annual Pitch Night Friday.

SipSafe is a date rape detection sticker that alerts users if their drink has been compromised. The group worked with mentor Casey Gum as well as scientists and professors to come up with a sticker that attaches to the back of a cell phone and is coated with chemicals that can detect the presence of date rape drugs.

StrawOne was named the People’s Choice winner and received $5,000 for their environmentally safe straw made from hay.
Photos by Nimai Malle

post_text:
Thank you to the Eanes ISD voters who approved an $80 million bond proposal! We will get to work on projects in safety & security, student programs & support, energy efficiency & conservation, and facilities, as well as new spaces for the Westlake High School aquatics and wrestling programs and expanded space for the robotics and engineering programs.

The voters approved the lone proposition at 82.5 percent.

In the Trustees election, Ms. Heather Sheffield won the unopposed race for Place 6, while Mr. James Spradley won the race for Place 4 with 56.5 percent and Ms. Ellen Balthazar won her seventh consecutive term in Place 7 with 79 percent.

post_text:
Happy Library Week and Library Month!
This is a great time to honor all the good work our librarians do across the district!

Our libraries circulated more than 200,000 books last year, served hundreds of classes, held 23 author visits, hosted all sorts of activities for students from STEM and Makerspace events to March Madness book contests to De-stressing and Mindfulness activities to book clubs and field trips for students and joint activities with the Westbank Community Library!

Our libraries contribute to building community for students and teachers! Thanks for all you do to support libraries and librarians. By supporting their work, you support student literacy, lifelong learning, and expanding the horizons of our students. We appreciate your support!

post_text: The Westlake High School Wrestling team traveled to Cedar Creek Elementary yesterday and read to second-grade classes, as part of a pilot program called Athletes as Readers. The goal is to get student-athletes into the elementary classrooms to connect with the young students and encourage them to read and be leaders in their schools. All of the books selected highlight positive Social-Emotional Learning messages like overcoming problems, healthy eating, kindness and friendship. All Eanes ISD libraries and schools will participate in the coming weeks. #EISDSEL #EISDShines #GoChaps Westlake Nation

post_text: Great job, West Ridge Middle School Future City students!
shared_text:
West Ridge Middle School
January 29, 2019 at 6:22 PM ·

Our Future City Engineering teams had a strong showing in the Regional Competition at UT-Arlington this weekend. Team Ochrona won first place, competing against 69 teams from around the state and will now head to Washington, DC to compete against the top teams from across the US, plus several international teams! Eanes ISD

Congratulations to:
Team "Invinciville" - "Best Use of Power Diversity Employing Nuclear"
Team "Evergreen" - "The "Riskonator" Award"
Team "Electropia" - "Best Residential Zone"
Team "Vigoropolis" - "Most Innovative Use of Construction Materials and Techniques"
Team "Ochrona" - "Best in Theme: Powering Our Future;" "People's Choice Award for Best Model;" First Place Overall

The Gift of Time, From a Man Dressed in RED

Throughout this school year, in all of my State of the District presentations, I am emphasizing the need to focus on the social-emotional wellness of our children and, for that matter, of our community. As one of our district’s strategic priorities, we believe schools are the heart of our community and we have a shared responsibility to make sure we create an oasis for the children in each of our schools. Read more: goo.gl/UkvE2t

post_text: Dr. Leonard visited with a special West Ridge Middle School student who is currently in the hospital. Gina Caro has been a leukemia patient for three years and has represented The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society as the girl of the year for two consecutive years. In an effort to spread the word about the work LLS does to fight cancer, the WRMS National Junior Honor Society is organizing school events to raise awareness and fundraise for LLS. We are proud of their efforts! #penniesforpatients

post_text: Interesting Westbank Community Library presentation tonight about our community's history!
shared_text:
Westbank Libraries
November 9, 2018 at 1:25 PM ·

Love local history? Come learn about the community we call home! Next Wednesday's Eanes History Night will include photos and narratives of families who founded this area in the 1870s, including personal accounts of rural life in the “Hills” from 1900 through the 1950s. You'll come away with a clear picture of how this area grew into our present-day community.

post_text:
We have identified ATS, BPE, CCE, EE, FTE, VVE, HCMS, and WHS are affected by the City of Austin’s boil water notice. Custodians will cover drinking fountains and bottled water will be delivered to the schools.

BCE and WRMS are in a different water district which has not been affected by the boil water notice at this time. We will continue to monitor the situation.

From Dr. Tom Leonard:
Conversations about school emergencies, and in particular school shootings, are not easy. While I do not enjoy these discussions, unfortunately, they are necessary. My hope is none of us will ever experience such a tragedy in our schools but it is our duty to be prepared.

See Dr. Leonard's full message on safety here: goo.gl/UN97QG

post_text: In spite of the traffic woes, we had a great turnout for our Realtors' Open House! Thanks to Westlake High School students and staff for putting on a fabulous tour and showcasing our wonderful programs!

post_text:
We have been informed that Bee Cave Road is open after a pretty tough morning for our buses, parents, students and staff. Thank you for your patience as we worked through this unplanned, unavoidable and frustrating issue!

Special thanks to our bus drivers and technology staff who were solid in their response. We appreciate their efforts and their service with a smile! #EISDShines
